    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-02-27T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-02-27T11:00:00-05:00" n="575"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d575">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">683.84A/2–2753: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 575<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Israel (<persName corresp="#p_DMB1"
                            type="from">Davis</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d575fn1">Repeated to Damascus, Jerusalem, London, Paris, and
                        Rome.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tel Aviv</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-02-27T18:00:00+02:00"
                            >February 27, 1953—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1380. <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 1370.<note n="2" xml:id="d575fn2">
                        <ref target="#d574">
                            <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> Embassy informed by Consulate General Jerusalem that true
                    text of letter sent from Lt. Col. <persName corresp="#p_GLC1">Gaon</persName> to
                        <persName corresp="#p_VH1">Vigier</persName> of <gloss target="#t_UNTSO1"
                        >UNTSO</gloss> reads as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“In view of the fact that it has been agreed to confine the present
                            Israeli-Syrian talks to changes of the demarcation line within the
                            demilitarized zones only, the Israeli delegation is expecting to be
                            notified of a date, settled by you, for the resumption of the
                            discussions.</p>
                        <p>“I have also been authorized to state that whenever an inhabitant of the
                            demilitarized zone elects to leave his present abode because of changes
                            effected in this zone, he shall be suitably compensated. If this
                            compensation is made in form of lands, such lands need not necessarily
                            lie within the demilitarized zone.”<note n="3" xml:id="d575fn3">
                                <p>In telegram 1383, Feb. 27, Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_DMB1"
                                        >Davis</persName> stated that <persName corresp="#p_SM2"
                                        >Sharett</persName> reported that <persName corresp="#p_VH1"
                                        >Vigier</persName> had informed an Israeli government
                                    representative that Syria was prepared to resume negotiations on
                                    the basis of the <persName corresp="#p_GLC1">Gaon</persName>
                                    letter quoted in telegram 1380. (683.84A/2–2753)</p>
                                <p>Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_MJS1">Moose</persName> reported
                                    from Damascus on Feb. 28 that the U.N. Truce Supervision
                                    Organization stated that the initial Syrian reaction to the
                                    Israeli reply was favorable. (Telegram 574; 683.84A/2–2853)</p>
                            </note>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DMB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
